WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.571 --> 00:00:05.740
<i>- Previously on</i> Marshals...
<i>- We got to hold</i>

2
00:00:05.807 --> 00:00:06.975
<i>on what we got.</i>

3
00:00:07.040 --> 00:00:07.909
We don't move.
it's Roner all over.

4
00:00:09.343 --> 00:00:10.712
<i>Said you'd been experiencing</i>

5
00:00:10.778 --> 00:00:12.514
some neck and shoulder pain?

6
00:00:12.580 --> 00:00:15.148
We'll run some tests.
try to find you some answers.

7
00:00:15.215 --> 00:00:16.483
Would you like to go
on a date sometime?

8
00:00:16.551 --> 00:00:17.652
I'd love to.

9
00:00:17.719 --> 00:00:19.119
Family name doesn't
carry water anymore.

10
00:00:19.186 --> 00:00:21.556
so you got to hide
behind a federal badge?

11
00:00:23.223 --> 00:00:24.526
<i>This...</i>

12
00:00:24.592 --> 00:00:27.996
- is a terrible idea.
- Long day.

13
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:35.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

14
00:01:26.320 --> 00:01:28.856
Winter fields came in nice.

15
00:01:28.923 --> 00:01:32.060
Yeah. Tom Weaver's hands
get all the credit.

16
00:01:32.125 --> 00:01:34.729
His daughter's hands
get credit. too?

17
00:01:35.495 --> 00:01:37.699
Hey. you communicating
with aliens?

18
00:01:37.765 --> 00:01:40.935
'Cause these hay bales
can't be for decoration. right?

19
00:01:41.002 --> 00:01:42.369
They're to feed the herd.

20
00:01:42.436 --> 00:01:44.404
Grass gets scarce
when the snow comes in.

21
00:01:44.471 --> 00:01:46.941
Get your hand warmers
ready. city slicker.

22
00:01:47.008 --> 00:01:48.408
Winter's coming.

23
00:01:48.475 --> 00:01:49.443
It's the first time
someone from Omaha's

24
00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:50.979
been slapped with that label.

25
00:01:51.045 --> 00:01:54.481
But I have you know. Tate.
I was freezing my ass off

26
00:01:54.549 --> 00:01:56.551
in the Hindu Kush when you
were still in diapers.

27
00:01:57.451 --> 00:02:00.454
Supposed to meet up with Deebo.

28
00:02:00.521 --> 00:02:02.255
Unless you got more grass
you want to stare at?

29
00:02:02.322 --> 00:02:04.726
Get out of here.

30
00:02:08.529 --> 00:02:11.264
Man. it's nice to see you two
doing so well.

31
00:02:12.332 --> 00:02:14.068
You know.
being a father suits you.

32
00:02:14.134 --> 00:02:16.037
Didn't come natural.

33
00:02:17.237 --> 00:02:19.206
I thought being somebody's son
would be the hardest thing

34
00:02:19.272 --> 00:02:20.842
I ever had to deal with.

35
00:02:22.476 --> 00:02:26.914
Man. I needed a morning
like this. Thank you. Coyo.

36
00:02:26.981 --> 00:02:28.382
Everything good?

37
00:02:28.448 --> 00:02:32.319
Yeah. just fighting battles
on multiple fronts. but

38
00:02:32.386 --> 00:02:34.088
it's nice to know
you got my six.

39
00:02:35.023 --> 00:02:37.525
Sketchy guy coming up
the driveway to the house.

40
00:02:57.310 --> 00:02:58.846
You lost?

41
00:02:58.913 --> 00:03:02.449
Not if I'm trying to figure out
where all the cowboys have gone.

42
00:03:02.517 --> 00:03:04.952
Think you can back up
that smart talk

43
00:03:05.019 --> 00:03:06.554
armed only with that six string?

44
00:03:06.621 --> 00:03:10.692
Ain't you heard?
I was born dangerous. Coyo.

45
00:03:19.067 --> 00:03:20.635
Damn. Double G.

46
00:03:20.702 --> 00:03:24.471
-I ain't seen you since...
-Camp Uhley. Afghanistan.

47
00:03:24.539 --> 00:03:25.673
So. after all this time.

48
00:03:25.740 --> 00:03:27.207
you just figured
you'd show up in Montana

49
00:03:27.274 --> 00:03:28.676
unannounced. huh?

50
00:03:28.743 --> 00:03:30.678
Well.
felt a calling to head west.

51
00:03:30.745 --> 00:03:33.280
see how my old teammate
was doing.

52
00:03:34.182 --> 00:03:36.249
Good Lord. is that Tate?

53
00:03:36.316 --> 00:03:37.885
Hey. Tate.

54
00:03:37.952 --> 00:03:39.821
I want you to meet Garrett. He's
my old buddy from the Teams.

55
00:03:39.887 --> 00:03:41.221
Figured.

56
00:03:41.288 --> 00:03:43.958
Can't imagine anyone else
getting a greeting like that.

57
00:03:46.861 --> 00:03:50.031
Cal? Wasn't expecting
to see you.

58
00:03:50.098 --> 00:03:53.768
Double G. In the flesh.

59
00:03:54.569 --> 00:03:57.572
I guess I should start
believing in ghosts.

60
00:04:00.074 --> 00:04:01.341
You were all teammates?

61
00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:03.745
Three-quarters of a badass group
of pipe hitters

62
00:04:03.811 --> 00:04:06.379
everybody called
the Four Musketeers.

63
00:04:06.446 --> 00:04:08.516
Nobody called us that.

64
00:04:09.282 --> 00:04:10.350
Who's the fourth?

65
00:04:16.224 --> 00:04:17.859
Let's. uh.
get your stuff inside.

66
00:04:17.925 --> 00:04:19.727
There's a lot to catch up on.
Ain't that right. Cal?

67
00:04:19.794 --> 00:04:24.132
I got something back at work.
It's good seeing you. Double G.

68
00:04:24.198 --> 00:04:25.800
Come on.

69
00:04:25.867 --> 00:04:28.770
Sure thing. boss.

70
00:04:29.871 --> 00:04:31.706
Get you inside. man.

71
00:05:15.883 --> 00:05:18.519
Hey. The fugitive

72
00:05:18.586 --> 00:05:21.354
we collared yesterday
was processed in Helena.

73
00:05:21.421 --> 00:05:23.157
And?

74
00:05:23.991 --> 00:05:26.160
And I thought
you'd want to know.

75
00:05:26.227 --> 00:05:28.796
Now I do. Thanks.

76
00:05:30.965 --> 00:05:32.200
You feeling okay?

77
00:05:32.266 --> 00:05:34.168
Yeah. yeah. Why wouldn't I be?

78
00:05:34.235 --> 00:05:38.471
Jared said your run-in was at
the doctor's office parking lot.

79
00:05:38.539 --> 00:05:42.176
-You left that detail out.
-I'm fine.

80
00:05:42.243 --> 00:05:43.978
Okay.

81
00:05:48.049 --> 00:05:49.650
Are we?

82
00:05:52.253 --> 00:05:55.156
We both agreed we made
a mistake and. you know.

83
00:05:55.223 --> 00:05:57.258
gonna respect boundaries
at work.

84
00:05:57.325 --> 00:05:58.793
Stay front-sight focused.

85
00:06:01.461 --> 00:06:02.730
It's nothing personal.

86
00:06:02.797 --> 00:06:05.132
Yeah. no. nothing personal.

87
00:06:07.235 --> 00:06:08.603
Right.

88
00:06:11.672 --> 00:06:14.842
Down.
Down. down. down. Good. Good.

89
00:06:14.909 --> 00:06:16.644
That horse has a fire
in his belly.

90
00:06:16.711 --> 00:06:18.946
I'd sooner jump on a grenade
than mess with him.

91
00:06:19.013 --> 00:06:21.215
Yeah.
he's got a temper for sure.

92
00:06:22.149 --> 00:06:24.685
I guess I would too if somebody
was trying to take my freedom.

93
00:06:24.752 --> 00:06:27.355
Well. I wish somebody
would've gave us this much TLC

94
00:06:27.420 --> 00:06:29.056
when we got out of the sandbox.

95
00:06:29.123 --> 00:06:32.392
All right. Come on. Come on.

96
00:06:38.366 --> 00:06:39.634
Good.

97
00:06:42.837 --> 00:06:46.173
I guess nobody gets off easy
getting out of the Teams.

98
00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:48.175
You had it worse than most.

99
00:06:49.677 --> 00:06:51.746
I look like I'm gonna
suck start my pistol to you?

100
00:06:51.812 --> 00:06:54.048
Just haven't seen you
in a decade.

101
00:06:55.049 --> 00:06:57.585
You were spinning out
pretty good last time I did.

102
00:06:58.786 --> 00:07:01.555
I ain't got a worry
in the world. Coyo.

103
00:07:01.622 --> 00:07:03.858
Trading in that rifle
for a guitar

104
00:07:03.925 --> 00:07:05.492
was the best decision
I ever made.

105
00:07:06.260 --> 00:07:08.896
Always did like
hearing you play that thing.

106
00:07:08.963 --> 00:07:11.966
I've been making a name
for myself up in Nashville. too.

107
00:07:13.768 --> 00:07:17.305
Glad you left the past
in the sandbox. brother.

108
00:07:17.371 --> 00:07:19.073
No looking
in the rearview for me.

109
00:07:19.140 --> 00:07:21.175
Music's my purpose.

110
00:07:21.242 --> 00:07:23.744
Seems you and old Cal
found a new one. too.

111
00:07:25.212 --> 00:07:28.082
I was spinning my wheels till
he offered me a Marshal badge.

112
00:07:28.149 --> 00:07:31.953
Ain't that rich.

113
00:07:32.019 --> 00:07:35.923
Cal gives you a new career.
and he ended mine.

114
00:07:39.126 --> 00:07:42.495
Well. all this reminiscing's
making me thirsty.

115
00:07:54.875 --> 00:07:56.310
Well. you know.

116
00:07:56.377 --> 00:07:59.013
only ten percent of first dates
make it to the third.

117
00:07:59.080 --> 00:08:02.316
Good for us.
beating the odds already.

118
00:08:03.150 --> 00:08:05.953
We got to survive
our fourth date

119
00:08:06.020 --> 00:08:10.057
before "us" makes it
into our vernacular.

120
00:08:10.124 --> 00:08:13.027
Not to get ahead
of anything. but. uh.

121
00:08:13.094 --> 00:08:15.129
are you thinking
about telling Cal?

122
00:08:16.330 --> 00:08:18.498
The man's got no say in my life.

123
00:08:19.300 --> 00:08:20.968
But he does in mine.

124
00:08:24.405 --> 00:08:26.140
Fine. How about now?

125
00:08:31.345 --> 00:08:34.248
- He just walked in. didn't he?
- Wait.

126
00:08:34.315 --> 00:08:36.584
So this is a-a thing?

127
00:08:40.621 --> 00:08:42.456
You got nothing to say?

128
00:08:43.391 --> 00:08:46.527
I didn't realize she was your
daughter when I asked her out.

129
00:08:47.762 --> 00:08:49.764
It's not something
I boast about.

130
00:08:57.905 --> 00:08:59.273
Enjoy your evenings.

131
00:09:09.316 --> 00:09:10.818
That charcoal filter.

132
00:09:10.885 --> 00:09:13.120
that's what makes it
Tennessee whiskey.

133
00:09:13.187 --> 00:09:15.389
Why are you pimping
Tennessee so hard?

134
00:09:15.456 --> 00:09:16.957
You said you were from Alabama.

135
00:09:17.024 --> 00:09:18.692
Well. I am.

136
00:09:18.759 --> 00:09:21.162
Only good thing
to come out of there is I-20.

137
00:09:21.228 --> 00:09:22.997
Myself included.

138
00:09:23.064 --> 00:09:25.166
I had to drag you out here
last week.

139
00:09:25.232 --> 00:09:26.967
now you're just
a regular. cowboy?

140
00:09:27.034 --> 00:09:28.669
I'm just playing tour guide.

141
00:09:28.736 --> 00:09:31.772
Garrett didn't appreciate the
peace and quiet at the ranch.

142
00:09:31.839 --> 00:09:33.841
Ugh. I get it.
I can't wait to get back

143
00:09:33.908 --> 00:09:35.910
to the concrete jungle myself.

144
00:09:35.976 --> 00:09:38.145
Fresh air is too suffocating.

145
00:09:38.212 --> 00:09:40.347
You know. I think you just
gave me my next song title.

146
00:09:40.414 --> 00:09:42.850
And that makes you my muse.

147
00:09:42.917 --> 00:09:44.185
You know.
last time I heard you play.

148
00:09:44.251 --> 00:09:46.854
you were interrupted
by a mortar attack.

149
00:09:47.688 --> 00:09:49.924
Taliban's a tough crowd. huh?

150
00:09:49.990 --> 00:09:51.492
They ain't got nothing
on those dive bars

151
00:09:51.560 --> 00:09:52.726
I've played down south. though.

152
00:09:52.793 --> 00:09:54.028
The stage is right there.

153
00:09:54.095 --> 00:09:55.963
You can finish
what you started for Kayce.

154
00:09:56.030 --> 00:09:59.200
I only play big venues
now. darling.

155
00:10:01.735 --> 00:10:05.272
Hey. Pull up a chair. Cal.
I'm buying.

156
00:10:07.775 --> 00:10:09.610
I think I'm gonna rain check it.

157
00:10:09.677 --> 00:10:10.945
After all we've been through.

158
00:10:11.011 --> 00:10:12.780
you can't sit down.
have one drink with me?

159
00:10:16.484 --> 00:10:17.885
Yeah. you know what?

160
00:10:17.952 --> 00:10:22.690
Next round. and the round
after that. is on me.

161
00:10:22.756 --> 00:10:24.625
Okay? Enjoy your night.

162
00:10:24.692 --> 00:10:26.861
Hooyah. Senior Chief.

163
00:10:29.897 --> 00:10:33.400
Well. here's to Two Musketeers.

164
00:10:33.467 --> 00:10:34.768
Cheers.

165
00:10:43.177 --> 00:10:44.979
Hey.

166
00:10:45.045 --> 00:10:48.482
Double G have you
howling at the moon last night?

167
00:10:48.550 --> 00:10:52.521
Took all my frogman skills just
to get him out of the Bullet.

168
00:10:52.587 --> 00:10:54.688
How is he?

169
00:10:55.890 --> 00:10:57.791
He's better than I expected.

170
00:10:57.858 --> 00:10:59.660
Seems to be all in
on this music thing.

171
00:10:59.727 --> 00:11:02.163
I mean. if he says so.

172
00:11:02.963 --> 00:11:05.534
Man shows up out of the blue.
after a decade.

173
00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:07.101
'cause life is good?

174
00:11:07.168 --> 00:11:08.537
Come on.

175
00:11:08.603 --> 00:11:10.104
I know a damaged frogman
when I see one.

176
00:11:10.171 --> 00:11:11.205
You should.

177
00:11:12.006 --> 00:11:14.074
You caused a lot of his damage.

178
00:11:26.621 --> 00:11:29.056
Hey. Tip just came in.

179
00:11:29.123 --> 00:11:31.892
Fugitive on our
Top 15 Most Wanted list.

180
00:11:31.959 --> 00:11:34.563
- Reed Pollard.
- Wait.

181
00:11:34.629 --> 00:11:37.566
The most wanted bank robber of
his generation is in our town?

182
00:11:37.632 --> 00:11:39.166
Planning his next heist.

183
00:11:39.233 --> 00:11:41.168
We got a possible
location on him.

184
00:11:41.235 --> 00:11:42.836
Yeah. I mean. Pollard's
been on the board for years.

185
00:11:42.903 --> 00:11:44.438
No one's come close
to catching him.

186
00:11:44.506 --> 00:11:47.408
Yeah. well. he's never been
on our hunting ground.

187
00:11:48.409 --> 00:11:49.910
Okay. Let's roll him up.

188
00:11:55.950 --> 00:11:57.586
Despite pulling off
some of the biggest heists

189
00:11:57.652 --> 00:11:59.720
of the last decade.
Pollard has managed to stay

190
00:11:59.787 --> 00:12:00.988
one step ahead of the Marshals.

191
00:12:01.055 --> 00:12:02.657
Yeah. this guy's
a modern-day Dillinger.

192
00:12:02.723 --> 00:12:04.693
His scores have netted millions.

193
00:12:04.758 --> 00:12:06.360
So what brings him to Montana?

194
00:12:06.427 --> 00:12:09.396
An anonymous tip says he's in
town scouting his next takedown.

195
00:12:09.463 --> 00:12:11.765
Bagging one of our most wanted.
that'd be a great way

196
00:12:11.832 --> 00:12:13.100
to start this day. y'all.

197
00:12:13.167 --> 00:12:14.636
- What's his target?
- We don't know.

198
00:12:14.703 --> 00:12:17.137
just that he's holed up
at the Ashford Rodeo Grounds.

199
00:12:17.204 --> 00:12:20.140
Rodeos have moved south for the
winter. Place will be deserted.

200
00:12:20.207 --> 00:12:21.442
Great. no civvies.

201
00:12:21.509 --> 00:12:23.377
Should we gear up.
full battle rattle?

202
00:12:23.444 --> 00:12:25.913
Pollard's not one to waste time.
so if he's moving on his target.

203
00:12:25.980 --> 00:12:27.348
I need you and Miles here.
quarterbacking.

204
00:12:27.414 --> 00:12:29.517
And. Andrea. you and Kayce.
you roll with me.

205
00:12:29.584 --> 00:12:30.951
Okay? Let's move.

206
00:12:33.555 --> 00:12:35.456
Did we just get benched?

207
00:12:35.523 --> 00:12:37.858
Sure feels like it.

208
00:12:37.925 --> 00:12:39.193
What'd you do?

209
00:12:39.260 --> 00:12:42.296
Nothing. You?

210
00:12:42.363 --> 00:12:43.897
Nothing.

211
00:12:43.964 --> 00:12:45.199
They're kicking doors.

212
00:12:45.266 --> 00:12:47.868
We're gonna get stuck here
doing paperwork.

213
00:12:51.805 --> 00:12:53.941
Nothing personal.

214
00:12:56.310 --> 00:12:57.646
Must have an inside connection

215
00:12:57.712 --> 00:12:59.213
to be holed up
in a place like this.

216
00:12:59.280 --> 00:13:01.115
Guy's stolen millions and
chooses to live like an animal?

217
00:13:01.181 --> 00:13:03.350
Lives like an animal
so he can steal millions.

218
00:13:03.417 --> 00:13:05.019
It's that kind
of discipline is why

219
00:13:05.085 --> 00:13:06.621
no one's come close
to catching him.

220
00:13:06.688 --> 00:13:07.955
How we want to do this?

221
00:13:08.022 --> 00:13:09.323
Pollard's known
for stealth. not force.

222
00:13:09.390 --> 00:13:11.325
so I think fast and dirty
should do it.

223
00:13:11.392 --> 00:13:13.127
Any word on his team?

224
00:13:13.193 --> 00:13:16.997
Usually only works with a few.
but n-never the same ones.

225
00:13:17.064 --> 00:13:18.932
Tip might be from
a scorned old crew member

226
00:13:18.999 --> 00:13:20.234
who's come back to haunt him.

227
00:13:20.301 --> 00:13:22.336
-Lot of that going around.
-Hey. Movement.

228
00:13:25.172 --> 00:13:26.006
On me.

229
00:13:34.315 --> 00:13:36.483
Federal agents. Show yourself!

230
00:14:07.716 --> 00:14:08.683
Contact rear!

231
00:14:17.424 --> 00:14:18.892
Go.

232
00:14:30.871 --> 00:14:32.841
Okay. hold fire.

233
00:14:32.906 --> 00:14:34.676
Check these bodies.

234
00:14:34.743 --> 00:14:36.143
U.S. Marshal!

235
00:14:40.615 --> 00:14:42.617
<i>Kayce.</i>
<i>none of these guys are Pollard.</i>

236
00:14:42.684 --> 00:14:44.218
<i>It's got to be yours.</i>

237
00:15:31.533 --> 00:15:34.101
Okay. Kayce and Andrea
are on the ground. searching.

238
00:15:34.168 --> 00:15:35.603
Where are we on Pollard?

239
00:15:35.670 --> 00:15:37.471
Local PD set up roadblocks.
three-mile perimeter.

240
00:15:37.539 --> 00:15:39.741
- Anything pop?
- No hits on the BOLO

241
00:15:39.808 --> 00:15:41.208
or at the perimeter checkpoints.

242
00:15:41.275 --> 00:15:42.710
Kayce says he clipped him.

243
00:15:42.777 --> 00:15:45.145
Have we checked hospitals.
local clinics?

244
00:15:45.212 --> 00:15:46.881
No gunshot wounds reported
anywhere within 30 miles.

245
00:15:46.947 --> 00:15:50.852
Gifford's gonna eat my lunch
if Bozeman PD get this collar.

246
00:15:50.919 --> 00:15:54.589
Did our fairy tipster happen
to come in with any more intel?

247
00:15:54.656 --> 00:15:56.490
He's gone radio silent.

248
00:15:56.558 --> 00:15:58.325
Okay. extend
to a statewide search

249
00:15:58.392 --> 00:16:00.628
'cause Pollard could've
stolen a car. slipped the net.

250
00:16:00.695 --> 00:16:02.396
- We can't lose him.
- Did you get anything

251
00:16:02.463 --> 00:16:04.364
from the three dead guys
you dropped?

252
00:16:04.431 --> 00:16:05.700
Still waiting on local PD

253
00:16:05.767 --> 00:16:07.167
to ID the guys

254
00:16:07.234 --> 00:16:09.504
'cause they were only carrying
guns and zip ties.

255
00:16:09.571 --> 00:16:12.907
Zip ties were likely
for hostages on their target.

256
00:16:12.973 --> 00:16:14.208
You may have
put them down right as

257
00:16:14.274 --> 00:16:15.677
they were launching their heist.

258
00:16:15.743 --> 00:16:17.010
Didn't put 'em all down.

259
00:16:17.077 --> 00:16:19.614
Yeah. don't remind me.

260
00:16:19.681 --> 00:16:21.315
And Pollard's the headliner
of this crew.

261
00:16:21.381 --> 00:16:24.919
It's unlike this team
to let such a big fish get away.

262
00:16:24.985 --> 00:16:26.453
Kicked the door
with a full unit.

263
00:16:26.521 --> 00:16:27.689
might've turned out different.

264
00:16:27.755 --> 00:16:30.357
Or maybe one of you
catches a round.

265
00:16:31.593 --> 00:16:33.093
You questioning my call?

266
00:16:33.160 --> 00:16:37.097
Not your call. your motive.

267
00:16:38.065 --> 00:16:40.167
My motive is to do
what's best for my team.

268
00:16:40.234 --> 00:16:42.169
and if you feel differently.

269
00:16:42.236 --> 00:16:43.905
that's on you.

270
00:16:44.672 --> 00:16:47.341
Now. we have a fugitive
on the loose.

271
00:16:48.810 --> 00:16:50.578
So. find him.

272
00:16:53.848 --> 00:16:55.082
Hey.

273
00:17:01.221 --> 00:17:03.658
Are you part
of this whole conspiracy?

274
00:17:03.725 --> 00:17:04.826
Oh. no. Man. no.

275
00:17:04.893 --> 00:17:08.530
The conspiracy to sideline me.
that's all you.

276
00:17:08.596 --> 00:17:12.466
I'm talking about
Miles and Maddie.

277
00:17:14.401 --> 00:17:18.138
They're... dating.
or whatever people do nowadays.

278
00:17:18.205 --> 00:17:21.141
Maddie's the girl
Miles had a crush on?

279
00:17:21.208 --> 00:17:24.779
Oh. Well. that explains
your grumpiness.

280
00:17:25.747 --> 00:17:27.047
At least towards him.

281
00:17:27.114 --> 00:17:28.583
Dating somebody I work with.

282
00:17:28.650 --> 00:17:30.250
Maddie's sticking it
to me. right?

283
00:17:30.317 --> 00:17:34.622
Sorry. it's... it's not
respecting work boundaries.

284
00:17:36.156 --> 00:17:38.325
Stay front-sight focused.

285
00:17:43.831 --> 00:17:45.934
Awful lot of firepower
Pollard's crew

286
00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:49.169
was packing today.
Not his M.O.

287
00:17:49.236 --> 00:17:51.305
He uses different tactics
for pulling off a heist

288
00:17:51.371 --> 00:17:52.774
and keeping his freedom.

289
00:17:52.840 --> 00:17:55.910
Man isn't willing to go quietly.
He made his choice.

290
00:17:55.977 --> 00:17:57.745
He got shot for it.

291
00:17:57.812 --> 00:17:59.681
Allegedly.

292
00:18:00.882 --> 00:18:01.916
I hit him.

293
00:18:02.717 --> 00:18:05.252
So in addition to your
SEAL and cowboy skills.

294
00:18:05.319 --> 00:18:07.220
you're also telepathic?

295
00:18:07.287 --> 00:18:09.991
Okay. who am I gonna
ask you about next?

296
00:18:10.058 --> 00:18:11.224
If you mention Dolly Weaver.

297
00:18:11.291 --> 00:18:13.260
you're walking home.

298
00:18:14.629 --> 00:18:17.431
Is that who has you checking
your phone every ten seconds?

299
00:18:18.465 --> 00:18:21.401
Garrett. actually.
He's not responding.

300
00:18:21.468 --> 00:18:23.605
Oh. he's probably just
sleeping it off.

301
00:18:23.671 --> 00:18:26.440
He was hitting it
pretty hard last night.

302
00:18:30.344 --> 00:18:34.582
911 reports an intruder
in a shed at 533 Marigold Road.

303
00:18:34.649 --> 00:18:36.651
That's four blocks
from the rodeo grounds.

304
00:18:37.451 --> 00:18:38.686
Told you I hit him.

305
00:18:40.088 --> 00:18:41.990
We'll see. cowboy.

306
00:19:08.650 --> 00:19:10.183
He's dead.

307
00:19:16.958 --> 00:19:18.492
That isn't Pollard.

308
00:19:27.434 --> 00:19:30.470
Dead guy Kayce and Andrea
found is Jack Manning

309
00:19:30.538 --> 00:19:33.440
from Pullman. Washington.
No priors.

310
00:19:33.508 --> 00:19:35.510
no known connection to Pollard.

311
00:19:35.576 --> 00:19:37.210
Okay. Where are we
with the rest of the crew?

312
00:19:37.277 --> 00:19:40.014
Troy Ryan. Kenny Roman.
Sam Harold.

313
00:19:40.081 --> 00:19:42.116
Ryan and Roman. both from Iowa.

314
00:19:42.182 --> 00:19:43.918
Harold from rural Michigan.

315
00:19:43.985 --> 00:19:45.687
And according to the FBI.

316
00:19:45.753 --> 00:19:48.122
none are known associates
to Pollard.

317
00:19:48.188 --> 00:19:49.456
Well. tough luck

318
00:19:49.524 --> 00:19:50.925
running into us on their
first time out with him.

319
00:19:50.992 --> 00:19:54.494
First time out anywhere.
They all have clean jackets.

320
00:19:54.562 --> 00:19:56.296
Clean jackets
don't mean clean living.

321
00:19:56.363 --> 00:19:57.799
True. but this ain't the crew

322
00:19:57.865 --> 00:19:59.701
that pulled off
the Lufthansa heist.

323
00:19:59.767 --> 00:20:01.035
Four strangers

324
00:20:01.102 --> 00:20:04.138
from out of state
with no criminal records.

325
00:20:04.204 --> 00:20:06.239
What are they doing in Montana?

326
00:20:06.306 --> 00:20:08.109
And where is Pollard
in all this?

327
00:20:08.176 --> 00:20:10.044
Could've been nearby when
you got the drop on his guys.

328
00:20:10.111 --> 00:20:11.378
slipped away.

329
00:20:11.445 --> 00:20:14.281
Or maybe he planned the job.
hired a crew

330
00:20:14.347 --> 00:20:16.017
while he stays in the shadows.

331
00:20:16.084 --> 00:20:18.285
Then who tipped us off
that he's in Bozeman?

332
00:20:18.351 --> 00:20:19.620
Wait. can we trace that tip that

333
00:20:19.687 --> 00:20:20.588
led us to Pollard
in the first place?

334
00:20:20.655 --> 00:20:21.989
It came from a burner phone.

335
00:20:22.056 --> 00:20:23.925
It's no longer pinging.

336
00:20:24.726 --> 00:20:27.227
I mean. Pollard's M.O.
has always been hands-on.

337
00:20:27.294 --> 00:20:28.663
so I know he's close by.

338
00:20:29.797 --> 00:20:31.933
We got to flip these four worlds
upside down.

339
00:20:31.999 --> 00:20:34.468
Maybe something will pop.
put us on to his whereabouts.

340
00:20:34.535 --> 00:20:37.404
And if he's the mastermind here.
then he armed these guys.

341
00:20:37.471 --> 00:20:39.272
Ballistics on the gun
might tell us a different story.

342
00:20:39.339 --> 00:20:40.641
Yeah. that's good thinking.

343
00:20:40.708 --> 00:20:42.409
Miles. Belle. you keep
digging into this crew.

344
00:20:42.476 --> 00:20:43.477
Let's get those
recovered weapons

345
00:20:43.544 --> 00:20:44.779
over to the ballistics lab.

346
00:20:56.124 --> 00:20:57.457
Where'd Kayce go. by the way?

347
00:20:57.525 --> 00:20:59.560
Said he needed to go
check on Garrett.

348
00:20:59.627 --> 00:21:01.028
Is something wrong?

349
00:21:01.095 --> 00:21:02.997
Couldn't get ahold of him.

350
00:21:06.266 --> 00:21:08.335
What is up with you
and Double G?

351
00:21:08.401 --> 00:21:09.804
He seems like a great guy.

352
00:21:09.871 --> 00:21:11.906
I thought the brotherhood
bonded you for life?

353
00:21:13.541 --> 00:21:15.710
Get these to the lab. okay?

354
00:21:16.944 --> 00:21:18.913
Oh. damn it.

355
00:21:18.980 --> 00:21:20.248
What's up?

356
00:21:20.313 --> 00:21:22.150
Look. there's. um. there's
something I forgot to do.

357
00:21:22.216 --> 00:21:23.818
Can you make this run solo?

358
00:21:23.885 --> 00:21:26.888
If it spares me your
yacht rock playlist. I got it.

359
00:21:26.954 --> 00:21:29.824
Look. and hey. make sure
they expedite the tests.

360
00:21:29.891 --> 00:21:32.026
-Okay?
-Hooyah. Senior Chief.

361
00:21:43.470 --> 00:21:45.773
Roner.

362
00:21:45.840 --> 00:21:47.141
Roner!

363
00:21:48.643 --> 00:21:51.411
Roner. I'm coming.

364
00:21:54.215 --> 00:21:55.750
Roner. I got you.

365
00:21:55.817 --> 00:21:57.652
- Hey.
- Coming. Roner.

366
00:21:57.718 --> 00:21:58.853
-Garrett.
-I'm coming.

367
00:21:58.920 --> 00:22:01.189
Hey. you're good.
Garrett. Hey.

368
00:22:01.255 --> 00:22:02.389
Get off me. Get off me.

369
00:22:02.455 --> 00:22:04.058
Get off me.

370
00:22:04.125 --> 00:22:06.493
-Garrett.
-Get off me.

371
00:22:07.728 --> 00:22:10.264
-Get off--
-Hey. Garrett.

372
00:22:10.330 --> 00:22:11.899
Garrett. you're good.
It's Coyo.

373
00:22:11.966 --> 00:22:14.535
Hey. It's Coyo. You're good.
You're good.

374
00:22:14.602 --> 00:22:17.872
Hey. hey. you're good. Hey. Hey.

375
00:22:17.939 --> 00:22:21.609
Hey. Hey. Yeah.
You're all right.

376
00:22:21.676 --> 00:22:24.212
Yeah. You're all right.

377
00:22:24.278 --> 00:22:26.814
You're all right. dude. Come on.

378
00:22:26.881 --> 00:22:29.116
You're good.

379
00:22:29.183 --> 00:22:31.351
You're good. You're good.

380
00:22:33.888 --> 00:22:35.523
Still not able to link
any of the shooters

381
00:22:35.590 --> 00:22:36.657
with Pollard or each other.

382
00:22:36.724 --> 00:22:39.227
No texts. emails. calls.

383
00:22:39.293 --> 00:22:40.995
I'm coming up empty myself.

384
00:22:41.062 --> 00:22:45.266
I can't even find evidence
that they were casing a target.

385
00:22:45.333 --> 00:22:46.734
I don't think failing Cal's

386
00:22:46.801 --> 00:22:48.669
gonna get me back
in his good graces.

387
00:22:48.736 --> 00:22:51.706
Sounds like you're at least
winning in your love life.

388
00:22:52.673 --> 00:22:54.441
-He told you about Maddie.
-Mm.

389
00:22:54.508 --> 00:22:55.843
How pissed is he?

390
00:22:55.910 --> 00:22:59.614
I wouldn't say
he's doing cartwheels over it.

391
00:23:01.716 --> 00:23:03.450
Story of my life.

392
00:23:03.517 --> 00:23:05.119
Good thing's always followed
by a bad one.

393
00:23:05.186 --> 00:23:09.190
Miles. you liked a girl.
you asked her out.

394
00:23:09.257 --> 00:23:11.092
she said yes.

395
00:23:12.093 --> 00:23:14.095
It's all good.

396
00:23:14.161 --> 00:23:15.997
No. it's not.

397
00:23:16.063 --> 00:23:20.167
My personal life's complicating
my relationship with my boss.

398
00:23:22.003 --> 00:23:23.470
Yeah.

399
00:23:23.537 --> 00:23:28.009
Well. I'm sure
it'll be awkward for a bit.

400
00:23:28.075 --> 00:23:29.810
but it'll blow over.

401
00:23:29.877 --> 00:23:34.682
Just when I started feeling like
I belonged at this job. now...

402
00:23:34.749 --> 00:23:38.451
Cal is only upset
because Maddie is into you.

403
00:23:38.519 --> 00:23:42.990
and she has been keeping him at
arm's length since he got here.

404
00:23:44.325 --> 00:23:47.295
Wait. how long have you known
Maddie's his daughter?

405
00:23:47.795 --> 00:23:49.630
Got some personal details there?

406
00:23:49.697 --> 00:23:53.200
No. I was just assuming things
aren't great with Cal

407
00:23:53.267 --> 00:23:55.670
because he had us going
to his daughter's bar

408
00:23:55.736 --> 00:23:57.437
without sharing why.

409
00:24:00.308 --> 00:24:02.677
We should get back to Pollard.

410
00:24:17.625 --> 00:24:19.492
I'll clear out now.

411
00:24:20.261 --> 00:24:21.762
Get out of your hair.

412
00:24:24.632 --> 00:24:26.867
Sorry for the trouble.

413
00:24:30.271 --> 00:24:33.473
We're all haunted by what
we did outside the wire.

414
00:24:34.976 --> 00:24:36.377
Or didn't do.

415
00:24:37.545 --> 00:24:40.114
You know. it's pretty twisted
how much more sense life makes

416
00:24:40.181 --> 00:24:42.950
in a war zone
than in the civilized world.

417
00:24:44.452 --> 00:24:47.021
I thought music
was your new purpose

418
00:24:47.088 --> 00:24:49.724
and you're out
doing what you love.

419
00:24:51.325 --> 00:24:54.528
Stopped doing what I love when
I got kicked out of the Teams.

420
00:24:56.630 --> 00:25:00.201
I used to be a part
of an elite combat unit.

421
00:25:00.267 --> 00:25:02.269
Now. I'm...

422
00:25:02.336 --> 00:25:07.341
scrounging for gigs up and down
the Honky Tonk Highway. and...

423
00:25:07.408 --> 00:25:08.909
grown tired of it.

424
00:25:09.543 --> 00:25:12.013
Man. they outed
all the quitters in BUD/S.

425
00:25:12.880 --> 00:25:14.715
You dragging
that guitar around tells me

426
00:25:14.782 --> 00:25:16.617
you're still in the fight.

427
00:25:18.252 --> 00:25:20.554
Music's my only escape.

428
00:25:20.621 --> 00:25:23.057
My only healthy one anyway.

429
00:25:23.824 --> 00:25:27.828
Yeah. when I'm on the stage.
that adrenaline. it...

430
00:25:27.895 --> 00:25:29.563
it helps me forget
about the past.

431
00:25:29.630 --> 00:25:32.199
but as soon as
the applause dies down...

432
00:25:33.601 --> 00:25:35.736
...I say good night to the sun.

433
00:25:39.640 --> 00:25:41.909
Things got pretty dark
for you. huh?

434
00:25:44.745 --> 00:25:46.247
In and out of jail.

435
00:25:47.314 --> 00:25:50.818
Psych wards. rehab.
sleeping on the streets.

436
00:25:52.720 --> 00:25:55.022
That last op changed everything.

437
00:25:56.424 --> 00:25:57.758
Yeah.

438
00:25:58.859 --> 00:26:00.895
For all four of us.

439
00:26:03.764 --> 00:26:05.933
You've taken
your hits. man. but...

440
00:26:07.301 --> 00:26:09.136
...you're a survivor.

441
00:26:11.072 --> 00:26:14.275
I feel like surviving's
my punishment for what I did.

442
00:26:16.043 --> 00:26:17.512
You may have a lot of demons.

443
00:26:17.578 --> 00:26:19.880
but don't go fighting
for something you didn't earn.

444
00:26:22.750 --> 00:26:25.052
We both know
who Roner's death is on.

445
00:26:27.188 --> 00:26:29.256
I'm trying to
get my head right. Coyo.

446
00:26:30.491 --> 00:26:32.126
I'm losing hope.

447
00:26:37.231 --> 00:26:40.234
I've dealt with a lot of hurt
and loss myself.

448
00:26:42.236 --> 00:26:44.305
This ranch helps.

449
00:26:45.106 --> 00:26:49.877
I may sing country.
but I ain't no cowboy.

450
00:26:49.944 --> 00:26:53.582
The healing power of nature.
that's-that's a real thing.

451
00:26:53.647 --> 00:26:57.151
Being out on the land.

452
00:26:57.218 --> 00:26:59.153
feel a part of it.

453
00:27:02.591 --> 00:27:03.924
It's been a long time

454
00:27:03.991 --> 00:27:06.026
since I felt like
I was a part of anything.

455
00:27:07.128 --> 00:27:08.362
Stay here.

456
00:27:09.396 --> 00:27:12.233
Long as you need until you

457
00:27:12.299 --> 00:27:14.735
find a path forward.

458
00:27:17.506 --> 00:27:19.907
You sure about that?

459
00:27:19.974 --> 00:27:21.610
I mean. I'm-I'm
a lot more complicated

460
00:27:21.675 --> 00:27:23.144
than that ornery horse.

461
00:27:26.714 --> 00:27:29.083
We might not be teammates
anymore.

462
00:27:30.451 --> 00:27:32.319
We're still brothers.

463
00:27:39.727 --> 00:27:41.195
I know it's a lot to take in.

464
00:27:41.996 --> 00:27:43.364
I'll loop in
a couple of specialists

465
00:27:43.430 --> 00:27:45.366
who have experience
with these kinds of cases.

466
00:27:45.432 --> 00:27:48.435
It's important
to know that you're not alone.

467
00:27:48.503 --> 00:27:51.305
Support groups can provide
a source of stability.

468
00:27:51.372 --> 00:27:53.040
especially early on...

469
00:28:17.064 --> 00:28:19.967
<i>Turn left in 400 feet.</i>

470
00:28:20.034 --> 00:28:23.871
Left ahead?
I already made two lefts.

471
00:28:39.119 --> 00:28:40.655
Mm. Hey.

472
00:28:40.754 --> 00:28:42.289
You didn't respond to my texts.

473
00:28:42.356 --> 00:28:44.124
Uh. I got sidetracked.

474
00:28:44.191 --> 00:28:47.261
Well. we didn't.
We located Pollard.

475
00:28:47.328 --> 00:28:48.530
Where was he hiding out?

476
00:28:48.597 --> 00:28:51.533
A jail in Las Cruces.

477
00:28:51.600 --> 00:28:53.000
New Mexico?

478
00:28:53.067 --> 00:28:56.170
Got picked up five days ago
under an alias.

479
00:28:56.237 --> 00:28:58.707
Small-town cops.
it took them a minute to realize

480
00:28:58.772 --> 00:28:59.708
they had bagged a whale.

481
00:28:59.773 --> 00:29:00.941
Why would someone tip us off

482
00:29:01.008 --> 00:29:03.310
about a fugitive
a thousand miles away?

483
00:29:03.377 --> 00:29:05.813
And Las Cruces cops say
they found nothing on Pollard

484
00:29:05.879 --> 00:29:08.650
pointing to any jobs in Montana.

485
00:29:09.450 --> 00:29:11.252
Did anything pop
on the rest of the crew?

486
00:29:11.318 --> 00:29:14.255
Still hard to figure out
what brought them here.

487
00:29:14.321 --> 00:29:18.759
and no evidence that they were
casing any spots for a heist.

488
00:29:19.960 --> 00:29:22.129
This is starting to feel
like a setup.

489
00:29:22.196 --> 00:29:25.600
Wait. did forensics get back
on the ETA with these results?

490
00:29:25.667 --> 00:29:27.201
No. nothing yet.

491
00:29:27.268 --> 00:29:29.236
Wh-- I thought you and Andrea
were doing that together.

492
00:29:30.337 --> 00:29:32.507
Yeah. I to-- I mean.
I told you. I got sidetracked.

493
00:29:32.574 --> 00:29:33.807
By what?

494
00:29:33.874 --> 00:29:38.145
Um... Just. uh.
get-get a sitrep from her.

495
00:29:49.490 --> 00:29:51.925
-Hey.
-Hey.

496
00:29:53.494 --> 00:29:55.664
Taking on one of those
battles you mentioned?

497
00:29:56.463 --> 00:30:00.501
Nah. I was just trying
to figure out if Pollard was.

498
00:30:00.568 --> 00:30:03.370
you know.
some kind of bait for us.

499
00:30:03.437 --> 00:30:05.406
You know?

500
00:30:05.472 --> 00:30:07.341
How's. uh. Garrett?

501
00:30:08.275 --> 00:30:11.278
He's still carrying a lot
of baggage. You were right.

502
00:30:12.514 --> 00:30:13.748
How bad?

503
00:30:14.415 --> 00:30:18.085
Sounds like he's gone Winchester
in his fight to keep going.

504
00:30:19.219 --> 00:30:21.188
And away from the chaos.
you know.

505
00:30:21.255 --> 00:30:23.457
these demons in your head.
they just

506
00:30:23.525 --> 00:30:24.759
keep grinding you down.

507
00:30:24.825 --> 00:30:26.561
especially if you don't got
teammates to lean on.

508
00:30:26.628 --> 00:30:27.796
Mm-hmm.

509
00:30:27.861 --> 00:30:29.997
And taking his bird
will do that.

510
00:30:30.064 --> 00:30:33.568
I tried everything.
everything. to avoid that.

511
00:30:35.202 --> 00:30:37.037
He's gonna stay with me
for a while.

512
00:30:37.104 --> 00:30:39.073
see if he can sort
some stuff out.

513
00:30:39.139 --> 00:30:40.407
You sure that's a good idea?

514
00:30:40.474 --> 00:30:43.010
Is "no man left behind"
not a thing for you?

515
00:30:43.077 --> 00:30:44.779
You know. he's my brother.
too. Coyo.

516
00:30:44.845 --> 00:30:48.550
And as his team leader. I feel
responsible for his struggles.

517
00:30:48.616 --> 00:30:51.985
but we both know
how combustible Double G is.

518
00:30:52.953 --> 00:30:55.122
I just don't want you
in his blast radius.

519
00:30:56.290 --> 00:30:58.626
It feels like we lost
two brothers on that op.

520
00:31:03.297 --> 00:31:04.532
- Hey.
- Hey.

521
00:31:04.599 --> 00:31:06.333
You heard back from Andrea?

522
00:31:06.400 --> 00:31:09.036
She's not answering her phone.
and the forensics lab said

523
00:31:09.103 --> 00:31:10.805
she never dropped
the weapons off.

524
00:31:11.305 --> 00:31:13.541
Miles is trying to get
a hit on her SUV.

525
00:31:13.608 --> 00:31:16.778
She should've been
there and back by now.

526
00:31:16.845 --> 00:31:18.979
Miles. what do you got?

527
00:31:19.046 --> 00:31:21.415
Sheriff found
Andrea's vehicle two miles

528
00:31:21.482 --> 00:31:23.183
- from the lab. smashed up.
- What?

529
00:31:23.250 --> 00:31:25.252
- Is she okay?
- There's blood

530
00:31:25.319 --> 00:31:26.920
in the vehicle.
but she wasn't on scene.

531
00:31:26.987 --> 00:31:28.355
What'd she hit?

532
00:31:28.422 --> 00:31:31.024
Truck hit her. broadside.
but it was also empty.

533
00:31:31.091 --> 00:31:32.393
Could be a hit-and-run.

534
00:31:32.459 --> 00:31:34.428
Did she run. too?

535
00:31:34.495 --> 00:31:37.264
Maybe she was in shock?
Wandered off.

536
00:31:37.331 --> 00:31:40.968
Or a Good Samaritan passed by
and took them all to a hospital.

537
00:31:41.034 --> 00:31:43.470
First we get ambushed
at the rodeo.

538
00:31:43.538 --> 00:31:44.839
now Andrea's missing?

539
00:31:44.905 --> 00:31:46.407
Feels coordinated.

540
00:31:46.473 --> 00:31:48.676
- DUSTWUN.
- What does that mean?

541
00:31:48.743 --> 00:31:50.344
Whereabouts unknown.

542
00:31:50.411 --> 00:31:52.413
Sheriff just sent over
traffic cam footage.

543
00:31:52.479 --> 00:31:54.381
All right.
Throw it up on the screen.

544
00:31:55.983 --> 00:31:57.685
There she is.

545
00:32:04.458 --> 00:32:06.661
That's no accident.

546
00:32:06.728 --> 00:32:08.162
Smash-and-grab.

547
00:32:08.228 --> 00:32:10.497
Classic ambush technique.

548
00:32:10.565 --> 00:32:12.232
My God.

549
00:32:13.066 --> 00:32:14.368
She's not moving.

550
00:32:14.435 --> 00:32:15.804
Yeah.

551
00:32:15.870 --> 00:32:17.438
Impact probably knocked her out.

552
00:32:19.874 --> 00:32:22.943
Okay. Okay. listen up. Hey!

553
00:32:23.010 --> 00:32:24.712
Hey. listen up!

554
00:32:25.613 --> 00:32:28.683
Deputy Marshal Andrea Cruz
has been abducted.

555
00:32:28.750 --> 00:32:30.217
So. whatever you're doing.

556
00:32:30.284 --> 00:32:32.252
getting her back
is our only priority.

557
00:32:32.319 --> 00:32:34.689
Okay? So you track her van.

558
00:32:34.756 --> 00:32:36.724
you ping her phone.
you do whatever it takes.

559
00:32:36.791 --> 00:32:39.159
Okay? No one's taking a break
till she gets back safe.

560
00:32:39.226 --> 00:32:40.662
No one. Let's go.

561
00:32:40.728 --> 00:32:42.664
Get to work!

562
00:32:44.398 --> 00:32:47.134
Hey. who the hell's
coming after us?

563
00:32:47.201 --> 00:32:49.671
Whoever it is.
it feels personal.

564
00:33:14.529 --> 00:33:18.131
Help! Help!

565
00:33:18.198 --> 00:33:20.100
Behave.

566
00:33:35.517 --> 00:33:37.852
Help! Help!

567
00:33:40.622 --> 00:33:43.925
Yell all you want.
No one's around to hear you.

568
00:33:47.562 --> 00:33:49.029
Stay there.

569
00:33:52.132 --> 00:33:53.500
Hey. Any luck
tracking her phone?

570
00:33:53.568 --> 00:33:55.102
Been trying to ping it.

571
00:33:55.168 --> 00:33:57.639
It's either turned off
or destroyed.

572
00:33:58.940 --> 00:34:01.141
Road weather cam
a few miles from the accident

573
00:34:01.208 --> 00:34:03.243
caught a cargo van
matching our BOLO.

574
00:34:03.310 --> 00:34:04.478
Okay. it's got to be
the same one.

575
00:34:04.546 --> 00:34:05.780
Got a hit on the registration.

576
00:34:05.847 --> 00:34:08.448
It's a business.
Treasure State Demolition.

577
00:34:09.249 --> 00:34:12.085
That's the first thing
that's made sense all day.

578
00:34:19.493 --> 00:34:22.764
Deputy U.S. Marshal Andrea Cruz.

579
00:34:23.798 --> 00:34:25.499
In my home.

580
00:34:27.234 --> 00:34:29.102
What an honor.

581
00:34:29.169 --> 00:34:31.940
Full force of the U.S.
government will be coming for me

582
00:34:32.006 --> 00:34:34.241
and you for breaking the law.

583
00:34:38.312 --> 00:34:39.847
Randall Clegg.

584
00:34:39.914 --> 00:34:43.952
After what your team
has done to my family.

585
00:34:44.018 --> 00:34:47.589
the only law that concerns me
is an eye for an eye.

586
00:34:52.192 --> 00:34:54.361
Stand up.

587
00:34:59.601 --> 00:35:02.570
Let's prep for a full assault
on Randall Clegg's compound.

588
00:35:04.072 --> 00:35:05.372
Would he grab Andrea
and take her

589
00:35:05.439 --> 00:35:06.841
to the first place we'd look?

590
00:35:06.908 --> 00:35:08.275
Even if she's not there.

591
00:35:08.342 --> 00:35:10.011
somebody on that property
will know something.

592
00:35:10.078 --> 00:35:13.480
What are the protocols
for an abducted U.S. Marshal?

593
00:35:13.548 --> 00:35:15.650
Tear Montana apart
till we find our teammate.

594
00:35:15.717 --> 00:35:18.853
I got a call into Gifford.
It's all hands on deck.

595
00:35:19.286 --> 00:35:21.288
What the hell is Clegg doing?

596
00:35:21.355 --> 00:35:22.857
Getting payback.

597
00:35:22.924 --> 00:35:25.093
Those zip ties we recovered
off the gunmen at the rodeo.

598
00:35:25.158 --> 00:35:26.426
they must've been meant for us.

599
00:35:26.493 --> 00:35:29.129
Going after Kayce's job
is one thing.

600
00:35:29.196 --> 00:35:33.034
but kidnapping a U.S. Marshal?
Why now?

601
00:35:33.101 --> 00:35:34.702
His business went bust.

602
00:35:34.769 --> 00:35:36.436
He lost the rare earth mine
demo contracts

603
00:35:36.504 --> 00:35:38.740
after his sons
shot up Broken Rock.

604
00:35:38.806 --> 00:35:41.375
With one son dead and another
one facing life in prison.

605
00:35:41.441 --> 00:35:42.476
he's got nothing to lose.

606
00:35:45.113 --> 00:35:46.480
Does an assault

607
00:35:46.547 --> 00:35:48.049
put Andrea at risk
if he's doing this to negotiate?

608
00:35:48.482 --> 00:35:50.551
Clegg knows
he's crossed the Rubicon.

609
00:35:50.618 --> 00:35:52.352
He is ready to go out
on his shield.

610
00:35:52.419 --> 00:35:53.755
Making himself a martyr

611
00:35:53.821 --> 00:35:55.890
certainly helps gain sympathy
for his son.

612
00:35:55.957 --> 00:35:58.660
I'm happy to oblige him.

613
00:36:01.529 --> 00:36:04.065
You know. I've been teammates
with Andrea for months now.

614
00:36:04.132 --> 00:36:06.934
I don't even know who to notify
as her next of kin.

615
00:36:08.903 --> 00:36:11.204
I think she said her mom
was back in New York.

616
00:36:12.707 --> 00:36:16.944
Right now. we're all
the family she's got.

617
00:36:17.011 --> 00:36:18.746
so let's get her home.

618
00:36:49.376 --> 00:36:51.278
What is this?

619
00:36:52.412 --> 00:36:54.549
A man standing his ground.

620
00:37:07.995 --> 00:37:10.497
This isn't a negotiation.

621
00:37:12.466 --> 00:37:16.904
Bit by bit. I've watched
the life sucked from this land

622
00:37:16.971 --> 00:37:21.341
by faraway bureaucrats
who care nothing for it.

623
00:37:22.176 --> 00:37:24.411
I've seen the blood of my kin

624
00:37:24.478 --> 00:37:26.848
spilled by their puppets.

625
00:37:28.348 --> 00:37:32.587
You all take and take and take

626
00:37:32.653 --> 00:37:35.857
till there's nothing left
but a desert.

627
00:37:36.858 --> 00:37:39.127
It has been too dry

628
00:37:39.193 --> 00:37:42.496
for too long around here.

629
00:37:53.406 --> 00:37:55.576
And what are you in all that?

630
00:37:59.781 --> 00:38:01.783
A spark.

631
00:38:06.687 --> 00:38:09.557
It's time to burn
the land clean.

632
00:38:23.171 --> 00:38:25.338
Why was Andrea alone
when she got grabbed?

633
00:38:26.507 --> 00:38:28.142
It was a routine run.

634
00:38:28.209 --> 00:38:29.844
I didn't know we'd be
in Clegg's crosshairs.

635
00:38:29.911 --> 00:38:32.479
Belle says you were
supposed to go with her.

636
00:38:32.547 --> 00:38:33.781
Yeah. and I would've sent you.
but you

637
00:38:33.848 --> 00:38:34.949
were more worried
about your old teammate

638
00:38:35.016 --> 00:38:36.383
than the ones you got now.

639
00:38:38.553 --> 00:38:40.688
Look. man. Roner. Double G.

640
00:38:40.755 --> 00:38:42.489
that is the third rail
in our friendship.

641
00:38:42.557 --> 00:38:44.058
but the only way Drea's
gonna get out of this

642
00:38:44.125 --> 00:38:46.561
is if we are pulling
in the same direction.

643
00:38:51.999 --> 00:38:55.335
It's eerie. though. 'cause the
last thing Drea said to me...

644
00:38:56.270 --> 00:38:58.506
...was. "Hooyah. Senior Chief."

645
00:39:01.341 --> 00:39:03.077
Garrett shows up
and here we are again.

646
00:39:03.144 --> 00:39:05.478
got another teammate
behind enemy lines.

647
00:39:07.480 --> 00:39:09.750
Let's hope this one
turns out better.

648
00:39:19.727 --> 00:39:21.596
This can't be
how Andrea goes out.

649
00:39:21.662 --> 00:39:22.797
Told you.
something good happens.

650
00:39:22.864 --> 00:39:25.365
something bad always follows.

651
00:39:27.735 --> 00:39:29.402
Coming up on the property line.

652
00:39:29.469 --> 00:39:31.138
<i>There's an</i>
<i>access road a few miles past</i>

653
00:39:31.205 --> 00:39:33.341
<i>the main entrance</i>
<i>to the Clegg compound.</i>

654
00:39:33.406 --> 00:39:35.977
<i>-We can jock up there.</i>
-Copy that.

655
00:39:44.719 --> 00:39:46.654
No signs of activity.

656
00:39:46.721 --> 00:39:48.589
-How far out is backup?
-Like an hour out.

657
00:39:48.656 --> 00:39:50.258
- but we can't wait for them.
- With any luck.

658
00:39:50.324 --> 00:39:52.526
we pull this together faster
than Clegg expected.

659
00:39:52.593 --> 00:39:53.728
Yeah. we catch them off guard.

660
00:39:53.794 --> 00:39:55.462
that's our best
tactical advantage.

661
00:39:55.529 --> 00:39:57.397
Okay. look.
we're gonna proceed on foot.

662
00:39:57.464 --> 00:39:58.733
fast and quiet.

663
00:39:58.799 --> 00:40:00.368
Belle. Miles. you're gonna take
the left flank.

664
00:40:00.433 --> 00:40:02.103
Kayce and I will take the right.
and when we get to the target.

665
00:40:02.169 --> 00:40:04.705
we're gonna clear
that main house first.

666
00:40:04.772 --> 00:40:06.807
I know we're all out for blood
right now. all right?

667
00:40:06.874 --> 00:40:08.676
But remember.
this is a hostage rescue. okay?

668
00:40:08.743 --> 00:40:11.579
So careful where you send
your rounds downrange.

669
00:40:11.646 --> 00:40:13.648
- Let's get our girl back.
- Let's go.

670
00:41:17.477 --> 00:41:18.879
Contact front!

671
00:41:22.450 --> 00:41:24.051
Down. down. down.

672
00:41:26.654 --> 00:41:28.622
We need fire on that bunker!

673
00:41:35.162 --> 00:41:36.764
Contact right!

674
00:41:36.831 --> 00:41:38.766
They were expecting us.

675
00:41:46.073 --> 00:41:47.975
Clegg went
and got himself an army.

676
00:41:55.249 --> 00:41:57.351
<i>More shooters in the barn.</i>

677
00:41:57.418 --> 00:41:58.886
They're gonna overrun us.

678
00:41:59.954 --> 00:42:01.555
<i>Watch the flank.</i>

679
00:42:04.291 --> 00:42:06.260
<i>We got to get off the X.</i>

679
00:42:07.305 --> 00:43:07.541
Do you want subtitles for any video?
